Pattern 4: Index Mapping
You need to track elements, but the distance between them (their indices) is the restricting factor.

The Concept: Store the array element as the key, and its index as the value. When you encounter a duplicate element, subtract its stored index from your current index to check the distance.

Java Blueprint:

Java
Map<Integer, Integer> indexMap = new HashMap<>();
for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
    // If we've seen it before, check the distance
    if (indexMap.containsKey(nums[i])) {
        int distance = i - indexMap.get(nums[i]);
        if (distance <= k) return true; // Condition met
    }
    // Update the map with the MOST RECENT index
    indexMap.put(nums[i], i); 
}
Essential Interview Questions:

Easy: Contains Duplicate II (LeetCode 219) - Find duplicates that are at most K distance apart.

Medium: Contiguous Array (LeetCode 525) - Here, you map the Prefix Sum to its index. If you see the same prefix sum again, the distance between the indices is the length of your valid subarray.
